# Design Spec — module `{{MODULE_NAME}}`

> One spec per vertical-slice module. This is the contract between "we understand the requirement"
> and "we can decompose it into build tickets." It is written AFTER the AC ledger exists and BEFORE
> the build plan. Cite the governing requirements throughout.
>
> **Design the data schema rigorously here, first.** Use the data-schema design method
> (`skills/data-schema/` — pluggable) to derive a normalized, constraint-backed model from the KB
> data catalog (effective-dated rows, append-only audit, polymorphic parents enforced by CHECK,
> non-overlap exclusion constraints) BEFORE you write the build plan. The contract layer is generated
> against this model, not hand-mirrored.

- **Module:** `{{MODULE_NAME}}` · **Owner globs:** see `MODULES.md`
- **Governing requirements:** `{{REQ_ID_PREFIX}}-*` in `{{KB_DIR}}/{{AREA_PATH}}/`
- **ACs in scope:** `AC-{{AREA}}-{{AC_RANGE}}` (from `{{AC_LEDGER_PATH}}`)

## 1. Context

What this module does, in two or three sentences, and **why** (cite the requirement). What it
deliberately does NOT do (scope boundary). Which other modules it consumes (shared-infra) and which
consume it.

