## 5. RBAC

Authorization is a capability matrix + row-level read-scope — never inline `if` checks.

| Capability | Roles that hold it | Row-level read-scope |
|-----------|--------------------|----------------------|
| `{{CAP_READ}}` | {{ROLES_READ}} | {{READ_SCOPE}} |
| `{{CAP_CREATE}}` | {{ROLES_CREATE}} | — |
| `{{CAP_UPDATE}}` | {{ROLES_UPDATE}} | {{UPDATE_SCOPE}} |

"To change who can do X, edit the matrix row for X" — record where that row lives
(`{{RBAC_MATRIX_PATH}}`).

## 6. Audit

| Audited field | Trigger | Audit row content |
|---------------|---------|-------------------|
| `{{FIELD_1}}` | on change | old → new, actor, timestamp |
| `{{FIELD_2}}` | on change | old → new, actor, timestamp |

One row per changed field; append-only; no in-band UPDATE/DELETE.

## 7. State machine

If this module owns a stateful entity, define its states and **guarded transitions** explicitly
(never a free `PATCH status`).

| From | To | Guard / who | Side effects |
|------|----|-------------|--------------|
| `{{STATE_A}}` | `{{STATE_B}}` | {{GUARD_AB}} | {{SIDE_EFFECTS_AB}} |
| `{{STATE_B}}` | `{{STATE_C}}` | {{GUARD_BC}} | {{SIDE_EFFECTS_BC}} |

Record where the transition map lives (`{{STATE_MACHINE_PATH}}`). Note cross-stage transitions
(transfer, handover, emergency, early closure) explicitly.

